17:23.560 --> 17:28.474
- ...4, 3, 2, 1...
- (grunting loudly)

17:28.560 --> 17:30.278
- (gunshot)
- (all cheering)

17:31.560 --> 17:32.656
TV announcer:
And they are off.

17:32.680 --> 17:37.390
The elite men in the 117th running
of the Boston Marathon,

17:37.480 --> 17:41.359
the oldest running marathon
in the United States.

17:41.440 --> 17:44.830
You can see that the crowd
has thickened to about four deep

17:44.920 --> 17:47.559
at some places there along
this course in Hopkinton...

17:56.320 --> 17:58.276
(video game chattering)

17:58.360 --> 17:59.952
Donohue,
are you on night vision?

18:00.040 --> 18:02.190
Why are you on night vision?
That's atrocious.

18:02.280 --> 18:04.396
And this guy owes me 20 bucks.

18:04.520 --> 18:07.239
Watch your hand, man.
And what do I owe you $20 for again?

18:07.320 --> 18:10.278
- 'Cause I talked to her.
- You didn't talk to her.

18:10.400 --> 18:11.976
Get the fuck outta here.
You talked to her?

18:12.000 --> 18:13.656
She said she's comin'
to the Zac Brown concert.

18:13.680 --> 18:16.114
- Big mistake.
- Nice MIT girl?

18:16.240 --> 18:17.798
She'll love it.
She'll be smitten.

18:17.880 --> 18:20.394
Gotta take her to something
classy, like the Pops.

18:20.480 --> 18:22.471
- The Pops?
- Yeah, the Pops.

18:22.560 --> 18:24.835
- Name one Pop.
- Beethoven. Done.

18:24.920 --> 18:26.512
Go to the barn!
Flank him, flank him!

18:26.600 --> 18:27.816
(country music playing on stereo)

18:27.840 --> 18:30.798
♪ Pop's farm was the place to go,
load the truck up, hit the dirt road ♪

18:30.920 --> 18:32.638
♪ Jump the barbwire,
spread the word ♪

18:32.720 --> 18:34.790
♪ Light the bonfire,
then call the girls ♪

18:34.880 --> 18:36.598
♪ King in the can
and the Marlboro Man ♪

18:36.680 --> 18:38.636
♪ Jack and Jim
were a few good men ♪

18:38.760 --> 18:40.376
♪ When we learned how to kiss
and cuss and fight, too ♪

18:40.400 --> 18:42.000
♪ Better watch out
for the boys in blue ♪

18:42.080 --> 18:44.799
♪ Chillin' on a dirt road ♪

18:44.880 --> 18:48.190
♪ Laid back,
swervin' like I'm George Jones ♪

18:48.280 --> 18:50.555
- Throw the flash bang! Throw...
- Got it!

18:50.640 --> 18:53.359
- You do this every time!
- You're in the way of the TV!

18:53.440 --> 18:54.440
Give me the fuckin'...

18:54.520 --> 18:57.398
- (crowd cheering)
- (panting)

18:57.480 --> 18:58.913
(bell ringing)

19:00.280 --> 19:03.431
Announcer:...took off so fast
that he almost caught the camera truck.

19:03.520 --> 19:05.416
Announcer #2:...on a course
that stretches from Hopkinton

19:05.440 --> 19:07.032
through Ashland,
Framingham, Natick...

19:07.120 --> 19:08.736
Announcer #3:
Desisa's to the right of your screen...

19:08.760 --> 19:11.376
Announcer #4:...back to the women
for a second, they got about six miles...

19:11.400 --> 19:13.136
Race announcer:
The elites have reached mile eight.

19:13.160 --> 19:14.388
Expected on Boylston Street...

19:14.480 --> 19:16.471
Paying my debt to society.

19:16.560 --> 19:18.596
- Oh, God...
- In the doghouse, huh?

19:18.680 --> 19:19.715
Yeah, but it's all right.

19:19.800 --> 19:21.256
He says it's the last hoop,
so we'll see.

19:21.280 --> 19:22.456
Get a haircut, though, will ya?

19:22.480 --> 19:24.755
Tommy: I'll cut my hair once
you stop shaving your legs.

19:26.720 --> 19:28.756
(Meng speaking Mandarin)

19:48.720 --> 19:50.392
Woman: Sorry!
Couldn't find my jacket.

19:51.000 --> 19:52.069
Ready to go?

19:52.160 --> 19:54.151
- Can we grab some drinks before we go?
- Sure.

19:54.240 --> 19:56.470
- Let's get "drunch."
- You don't have to beg me.

19:57.640 --> 19:59.336
Announcer:...and as all
the contenders are in there,

19:59.360 --> 20:00.616
and they're closing hand over fist.

20:00.640 --> 20:02.949
TV reporter:
Kogo, Desisa, and Gabremariam.

20:03.040 --> 20:05.110
So Ethiopia has two of the three.

20:05.200 --> 20:06.235
(indistinct chattering)

20:08.000 --> 20:09.752
- Man: Ready, man?
- Boy: Yes, Daddy.

20:09.840 --> 20:11.239
- You are?
- Yeah.

20:11.320 --> 20:13.470
- Wanna go see Mommy at the race?
- Yeah!

20:13.560 --> 20:14.960
Wanna go cheer on Mommy
at the race?

20:17.160 --> 20:19.196
Let's roll. Let's roll.

20:20.520 --> 20:21.589
All right.

20:22.760 --> 20:23.760
Yes.

20:26.240 --> 20:29.471
TV announcer:...and running one of
the most famous streets in Boston...

20:29.560 --> 20:31.456
Race announcer:
The front-runners are approaching mile 23!

20:31.480 --> 20:33.755
We're mere minutes away
from crowning the winner

20:33.840 --> 20:37.196
- of the 2013 Boston Marathon.
- Get some people outta here.

20:37.280 --> 20:39.016
This is against fire code.
We got way too many people.

20:39.040 --> 20:40.678
- She can stay.
- Thanks, Tommy.

20:40.800 --> 20:42.518
How are you?
How's your husband, good?

20:42.600 --> 20:43.640
He's good.
He's doing fine.

20:43.720 --> 20:46.632
(indistinct chattering)

20:46.720 --> 20:48.736
Announcer: Again, you're looking
at Heartbreak Hill now.

20:48.760 --> 20:50.216
Announcer #2:
We're leaving the elites now.

20:50.240 --> 20:52.151
(crowd cheering)

20:54.960 --> 20:56.109
Announcer #3:
Kenmore Square.

20:56.200 --> 20:58.080
You see the light stanchions
over that building.

20:58.760 --> 21:01.069
This is one of the really cool
spots in Boston...

21:01.160 --> 21:03.628
Announcer #4: And look at that,
the Boston Marathon running

21:03.720 --> 21:06.518
right past Fenway Park,
which will soon empty out...

21:06.600 --> 21:08.670
(crowd cheering)

21:11.720 --> 21:15.076
(indistinct sports
commentary on TV)

21:15.160 --> 21:17.469
(indistinct chattering)

21:22.920 --> 21:25.136
Announcer #4:...making the right turn,
they're heading up towards Boylston.

21:25.160 --> 21:28.755
Announcer #5: Looks like Ethiopia
is gonna reign supreme!

21:28.840 --> 21:30.096
Announcer #6:
And here they come!

21:30.120 --> 21:31.838
Heading down Boylston
for the last block!

21:31.920 --> 21:34.036
Announcer #7:
Is there anyone else on the road?

21:34.120 --> 21:35.633
Announcer #8:
Very fast time.

21:35.720 --> 21:38.075
- (helicopter hovering)
- Woman: Standby, camera three..

21:38.160 --> 21:40.355
Three, two, one...

21:40.440 --> 21:41.555
and lead the way.

21:41.640 --> 21:44.473
Race announcer:
Desisa is the 2013

21:44.560 --> 21:47.313
- champion of the elites.
- (cheering)

21:47.400 --> 21:49.675
(indistinct announcer on P.A.)

22:04.520 --> 22:07.281
Announcer #9: Time to take in
what the Boston Marathon is truly about.

22:08.960 --> 22:12.111
Watching thousands of amateur athletes
complete the amazing feat.

22:12.200 --> 22:14.760
(indistinct announcement on P.A.)

22:14.840 --> 22:17.149
(crowd cheering)

22:17.240 --> 22:19.629
I'd think about losin'
that Yankees cap.

22:19.720 --> 22:22.600
You got a lot of Sox fans in these bars.
I'd hate to see ya get tuned up.

22:22.640 --> 22:25.598
(marching band playing)

22:28.800 --> 22:30.074
Oh.

22:30.640 --> 22:34.076
Announcer: And say hello to Frank Night,
from Boston, Massachusetts.

22:34.520 --> 22:35.919
- (camera clicks)
- Thanks.

22:36.840 --> 22:38.671
(indistinct announcements on P.A.)

22:42.000 --> 22:43.911
Man: Excuse me.
Sorry. Sorry 'bout that.

22:44.000 --> 22:45.194
Please excuse me.

22:45.280 --> 22:48.590
Race announcer: That's Police Chief
Billy Evans crossing the finish line!

22:49.160 --> 22:50.275
Way to go, Billy!

22:50.360 --> 22:51.952
- Thank you, Governor.
- Nice job.

22:53.640 --> 22:56.518
Race announcer: Does anybody
have a big tub of melted butter?

22:56.600 --> 22:59.717
A huge lobster
just crossed the finish line!

23:02.560 --> 23:05.597
(indistinct announcement on P.A.)

23:07.840 --> 23:09.432
Hey! Leo...

23:11.040 --> 23:13.429
- Time out.
- No time out!

23:32.240 --> 23:34.435
- Hey!
- Baby...

23:34.520 --> 23:36.238
- You behavin' yourself?
- Oh, yeah.

23:36.320 --> 23:37.435
Here it is, you numbskull.

23:37.560 --> 23:39.016
You're on your feet all day,
and you wear the wrong one?

23:39.040 --> 23:41.216
I did it on purpose so you'd have to
bring me the fatter one.

23:41.240 --> 23:43.959
- Romantic, right?
- I'm sure that was your plan!

23:44.040 --> 23:46.520
- You wanna walk with me a bit?
- No, I gotta get back to work!

23:46.560 --> 23:47.960
I gotta claw my way outta this zoo!

23:48.040 --> 23:50.160
- I love you. Thanks for the brace.
- I love you, too.

23:50.280 --> 23:51.395
Hey, give that to Joey.

23:51.480 --> 23:53.311
(crowd continues cheering)

24:20.200 --> 24:21.599
Announcer:
Looking down Boylston,

24:21.680 --> 24:24.200
you can see waves of runners
turning the corner for the final...

24:24.760 --> 24:27.069
(crowd cheering)

24:42.120 --> 24:43.951
Did you see that guy?
(laughs)

24:56.320 --> 24:59.835
There he is.
General Patton in a neon vest.

24:59.920 --> 25:02.416
Hey, Commish, I'll get a fuckin' smoothie
and be waitin' in the back

25:02.440 --> 25:03.555
of the Tahoe for you and Q.

25:03.640 --> 25:05.471
- (laughing)
- Hey, grab this bozo!

25:05.560 --> 25:07.915
Get him outta here!
Keep your eyes open, will ya?

25:08.000 --> 25:09.718
(crowd continues cheering)

25:13.240 --> 25:14.696
I'm proud of ya, Tommy.
How ya feelin'?

25:14.720 --> 25:16.312
The knee hurts.
The back hurts.

25:16.400 --> 25:17.992
The balls hurt.
The pain sometimes feels

25:18.080 --> 25:19.256
like it hurts
on top of the hurt,

25:19.280 --> 25:20.456
- if that's even remotely possible.
- (cell phone rings)

25:20.480 --> 25:22.675
This is Davis.

25:22.760 --> 25:24.591
No, the Biden call's
scheduled for 3:00.

25:24.680 --> 25:26.456
Biden? Vice President Biden?
Hey, let me talk to him.

25:26.480 --> 25:28.914
- Behave yourself, Tommy.
- Commissioner, let me talk to him!

25:29.000 --> 25:30.558
Guys! The lobster's back!

25:30.640 --> 25:32.517
Come here!
Cuff that lobster, will you?

25:35.840 --> 25:38.229
(indistinct radio chatter)

25:39.560 --> 25:40.754
Whoo!

25:43.880 --> 25:46.394
(indistinct announcement on P.A.)

25:53.840 --> 25:56.559
Announcer: The finalists
in the wheelchair competition here...

25:58.080 --> 26:00.680
Announcer #2:...very fast runners
here out on this storied course.

26:00.720 --> 26:02.278
So much history today.

26:02.360 --> 26:05.033
To all the runners
and our team behind the scenes,

26:05.120 --> 26:07.156
thank you for bringing this race...

26:14.360 --> 26:16.590
- (alarms blaring)
- (people screaming)

26:44.720 --> 26:46.870
Those are bombs, Captain!
Those are bombs!

26:47.280 --> 26:49.840
This is Delta 984!
We got multiple explosions! We need...

26:49.960 --> 26:52.155
(alarm blaring)

26:57.360 --> 26:59.112
(clamoring)

27:16.640 --> 27:18.835
(child crying)

27:23.800 --> 27:25.233
(screaming)

27:41.760 --> 27:42.760
Shit!

27:46.120 --> 27:48.190
(indistinct shouting)

27:55.000 --> 27:58.470
All medical personnel
to the finish line! Now!

27:58.560 --> 28:00.312
Something just exploded
at the finish line.

28:00.400 --> 28:02.311
What did he say?
Let's turn around, Q.

28:02.400 --> 28:03.594
(tires screeching)

28:10.800 --> 28:12.791
I repeat, multiple casualties!

28:12.880 --> 28:14.472
(woman sobbing)

28:15.400 --> 28:16.400
I got you.

28:17.160 --> 28:19.594
Sir, you're gonna be okay, all right?
You're gonna be okay.

28:21.320 --> 28:23.000
Ma'am, hold on to this
as tight as you can.

28:23.040 --> 28:25.076
Hey, get that wheelchair
over here now!

28:25.760 --> 28:27.876
All medical personnel
to the finish line!

28:29.880 --> 28:32.269
- We need two over here!
- Repeat, multiple casualties!

28:32.360 --> 28:34.669
- Carol: Tommy!
- Carol!

28:34.760 --> 28:37.911
- You okay? Huh? Lemme see.
- (crying)

28:38.360 --> 28:40.874
All right. You're okay. You're okay.
Hey, Sully, come here!

28:40.960 --> 28:43.428
Carol, go with him now!
Get her home now!

28:43.520 --> 28:44.748
Dispatch:
Repeat your location!

28:44.840 --> 28:46.751
This is Delta 984!
I'm at the finish line!

28:46.840 --> 28:48.520
Dispatcher:
I only wanna hear from the 984!

28:48.560 --> 28:50.278
I only wanna hear
from that supervisor.

28:50.360 --> 28:51.536
All right, this is what I need.

28:51.560 --> 28:54.028
I want Ring Road clear,
so I can push ambulances in and out!

28:54.160 --> 28:55.718
Keep pushin' in those ambulances!

29:02.920 --> 29:04.797
(indistinct radio chatter)

29:06.440 --> 29:07.998
(sirens wailing)

29:08.600 --> 29:10.556
Okay. People are coming.

29:17.640 --> 29:20.552
Ma'am, you're on fire.
That's it.

29:22.200 --> 29:24.668
(people groaning)

29:26.440 --> 29:27.668
Man: Oh, shit!

29:31.400 --> 29:32.515
Man: Sir?

29:32.600 --> 29:34.989
Can we get some help, sir?
Anyone, sir, please?

29:35.080 --> 29:36.080
Yeah.

29:38.240 --> 29:40.470
You're okay. You're okay.

29:40.560 --> 29:41.834
- (crying)
- You're okay.

29:46.000 --> 29:47.760
We gotta take your son
and get him some help.

29:48.880 --> 29:50.472
Leo! Leo!

29:53.800 --> 29:55.358
You're gonna be okay, sir.

30:00.560 --> 30:02.596
You all right? You hear me?

30:03.480 --> 30:04.480
You're okay.

30:05.800 --> 30:06.915
I can't...

30:07.000 --> 30:08.228
Man:
We'll figure this out.

30:09.000 --> 30:11.958
- I'll find you in just a minute.
- Jess...

30:12.080 --> 30:14.036
(sirens wailing)

30:16.520 --> 30:17.839
Get the wheelchairs!
Come on!

30:20.800 --> 30:23.075
(helicopter hovering)

30:25.960 --> 30:27.720
EMT: Both of her legs
are severely lacerated.

30:28.800 --> 30:30.240
- On three, ready?
- This is my wife.

30:30.280 --> 30:31.395
She's gonna be okay.

30:35.000 --> 30:37.719
Hey! Send two more ambulances
from Ring Road right now!

30:37.800 --> 30:40.394
On radio: This is Sergeant Davis
at the Forum Cafe.

30:40.480 --> 30:42.869
I need personnel at
the second bomb site immediately!

30:44.320 --> 30:45.753
I need assistance!

30:45.840 --> 30:48.070
(panting)

30:48.600 --> 30:51.558
This is Delta 984.
I'm heading to the second bomb site!

30:51.640 --> 30:53.471
Everybody, keep this line clear!

30:53.560 --> 30:57.758
And stop letting runners through!
Secure the perimeter!

30:57.840 --> 31:00.718
If I see another runner,
your ass is done!

31:10.880 --> 31:12.836
Woman: We need a fuckin'
ambulance over here!

31:12.920 --> 31:14.920
We need ambulances down
at the second bombing site!

31:15.000 --> 31:16.558
Starbucks and the Forum!

31:16.640 --> 31:18.320
Are there more bombs?
Are there more bombs?

31:18.360 --> 31:19.816
No, no, no, no.
Look at me. You're gonna be okay.

31:19.840 --> 31:21.976
- You're doin' good, all right?
- What's that? What's that?

31:22.000 --> 31:23.680
Don't look at that!
Look at me! Look at me!

31:23.760 --> 31:25.159
Get that over here now!

31:25.240 --> 31:27.674
Guys, shut down the race!

31:27.760 --> 31:30.513
Do not have another person
run down Boylston Street!

31:30.600 --> 31:32.795
Come on, get her up, get her up!
Shut down the race!

31:32.880 --> 31:35.348
Fuck, Tommy!
We've got two fatalities.

31:35.440 --> 31:38.159
We got two fatalities,
and a fuckin' kid, eight years old.

31:38.240 --> 31:39.336
- Where's his family?
- They're wounded.

31:39.360 --> 31:40.656
They fuckin' dragged
everybody out.

31:40.680 --> 31:42.816
- For fuck's sake, what do we do?
- I don't fuckin' know.

31:42.840 --> 31:45.056
We gotta leave someone with him.
We cannot leave him here alone, Captain.

31:45.080 --> 31:46.216
No, we're gonna get
someone by his side.

31:46.240 --> 31:47.376
- I ain't goin anywhere.
- We need everybody

31:47.400 --> 31:48.496
out of the area immediately.

31:48.520 --> 31:49.936
We gotta clear the perimeter.
Could be more bombs.

31:49.960 --> 31:50.960
Yeah, I'm on it.

31:53.440 --> 31:54.440
Hey!

31:55.080 --> 31:56.991
Anyone in here? Anyone?

32:06.640 --> 32:08.119
- Shit!
- (cell phone chimes)

32:12.120 --> 32:14.509
This is Delta 984.
We gotta confiscate all cell phones.

32:14.600 --> 32:17.720
Repeat. If you see anyone recordin',
grab their phones, I don't care who it is!

32:19.640 --> 32:20.789
Man:
They gotta find my boy.

32:20.880 --> 32:23.189
Somebody, please...

32:23.280 --> 32:24.838
EMT: Don't worry.
We'll find him, sir.

32:24.960 --> 32:26.439
I don't know where he is.

32:36.000 --> 32:38.036
(indistinct on radio)

32:39.480 --> 32:41.216
Lee, I'm James. I'm going to
take care of you, all right?

32:41.240 --> 32:42.309
You're going to be fine.

32:46.680 --> 32:49.114
(indistinct chattering)

32:53.280 --> 32:55.794
Nurse: Can you feel that?
Can you wiggle your toes?

32:56.800 --> 32:58.631
Good. Good, good, good.
We're good.

32:58.720 --> 33:00.280
Doctor:
We're gonna save your leg, okay?

33:00.320 --> 33:02.390
Hey, you gotta help me
find my son.

33:02.480 --> 33:05.517
His name is Leo Woolfenden.
He's three years old.

33:05.600 --> 33:07.511
We got separated somehow.
Somebody took him.

33:07.600 --> 33:09.636
I just didn't...
You need to find him.

33:09.720 --> 33:14.032
His name is Leo Woolfenden.
W-O-O-L...

33:24.680 --> 33:26.736
Tommy: Push out and make sure
we're keepin' people out of the perimeter.

33:26.760 --> 33:29.593
- All right? Get moving.
- We've got a six-block perimeter set up.

33:29.680 --> 33:32.035
- We're all locked down here.
- (sirens wailing)

33:34.880 --> 33:38.998
Oh, boy.
Here we go. Here we go.

34:17.520 --> 34:19.397
- This is the first blast scene?
- Tommy: Yeah.

34:19.480 --> 34:20.976
The second was down there
at the Forum restaurant.

34:21.000 --> 34:23.416
- Bradshaw: Total station en route.
- Okay, we need TEDAC and OPU.

34:23.440 --> 34:26.096
- What about cell phones, cameras?
- Yeah, we're right on top of that.

34:26.120 --> 34:27.775
Yeah, we're collecting cell phones,
surveillance tapes,

34:27.800 --> 34:30.295
- all the video we can find.
- Get 'em all, Tommy. Don't miss any.

34:30.320 --> 34:31.456
How big is the secured perimeter?

34:31.480 --> 34:32.856
Six blocks off the course
each direction.

34:32.880 --> 34:35.030
- Let's extend that. Make it 10.
- You got it.

34:35.120 --> 34:37.136
It's clearly coordinated.
There could be more bombs.

34:37.159 --> 34:40.277
- How many total wounded?
- Got three fatalities that we know of.

34:40.360 --> 34:42.954
One's a little child on the street
in front of the Forum.

34:43.040 --> 34:45.793
- (clattering)
- What are they doin'?

34:45.880 --> 34:47.856
What? I said that's
an eight-year-old kid under there.

34:47.880 --> 34:49.536
No, they can't move the body.
We've gotta clear them out.

34:49.560 --> 34:50.616
Tell them to clear out of there!

34:50.639 --> 34:51.896
- You got it, you got it.
- Tell them to clear out of there.

34:51.920 --> 34:53.416
- Who the fuck are you?
- Sorry, Sergeant.

34:53.440 --> 34:56.591
Could be clues in the blood-splattered
bomb residue on the boy's body.

34:56.679 --> 34:58.352
We can't risk moving him.
Nothing moves.

34:58.440 --> 35:00.336
What's the matter with you guys?
You gonna tell that boy's parents

35:00.360 --> 35:02.216
that their son's still
lyin' on the fuckin' street?

35:02.240 --> 35:03.696
- Turn it down, Tommy.
- Oh, fuck that!

35:03.720 --> 35:05.950
- Tommy! Let's go over there.
- All right, Billy...

35:06.080 --> 35:07.520
Just fuckin' leave me alone,
will ya?

35:07.560 --> 35:11.473
We've gotta decide who's running this,
and we have to decide quickly.

35:11.560 --> 35:13.391
If it's terrorism,
it's yours, Rick.

35:13.480 --> 35:16.711
Gentlemen, the moment we label
this terrorism, everything changes.

35:16.840 --> 35:19.718
It's not about Boston anymore.
It's not a local investigation.

35:19.800 --> 35:22.109
It's Wolf Blitzer.
It's stock markets.

35:22.200 --> 35:26.990
It's politicians and knee-jerk reactions,
anti-Muslim backlash...

35:27.080 --> 35:28.399
And what if we're wrong?

35:28.520 --> 35:30.656
I mean, there's no take-back.
I've been through this before.

35:30.680 --> 35:32.750
Look, your call,
but we already know it is.

35:32.840 --> 35:35.229
And a cell is activated,
they hit Chicago or New York

35:35.360 --> 35:36.839
or Washington,
what happens then?

35:36.920 --> 35:39.388
The accusations are gonna come,
no matter what we do.

36:00.480 --> 36:02.152
(clatters)

36:02.240 --> 36:04.515
It's terrorism.
We'll take it.

36:07.200 --> 36:09.111
So, what do you need?

36:10.080 --> 36:13.117
Command center.
Really big one.

36:14.160 --> 36:16.151
- (sirens wailing)
- (helicopter hovering)

36:32.120 --> 36:33.792
This'll do.

36:35.640 --> 36:37.471
I want CART team over there.

36:37.560 --> 36:39.835
Post-blast investigators
in that corner.

36:39.920 --> 36:41.592
We need a media tent set up.

36:41.680 --> 36:43.160
All right, let's get an evidence grid

36:43.240 --> 36:45.231
started right over there
against that wall.

36:45.320 --> 36:47.595
And I guarantee
these are gonna crash,

36:47.680 --> 36:49.910
so let's get a bank of
landlines up immediately.

36:50.000 --> 36:51.752
We're good, boss.
We'll be up in an hour.

36:51.840 --> 36:52.875
(reporters clamoring)

36:52.960 --> 36:54.896
Reporter: Commissioner Davis,
the "New York Post" is reporting

36:54.920 --> 36:57.673
a 20-year-old Saudi national
has been charged.

36:57.760 --> 36:59.432
- Can you confirm?
- That is false.

36:59.520 --> 37:01.750
We have not charged
anyone at this time.

37:01.840 --> 37:05.230
We are asking the public to help us
supplement the investigation.

37:05.320 --> 37:07.914
Anyone with photos
or video of the marathon

37:08.000 --> 37:10.639
is encouraged to turn them in
to Boston Police.

37:10.720 --> 37:12.392
(indistinct chattering)

37:12.480 --> 37:14.736
I need you to give me access
to the following databases...

37:14.760 --> 37:16.159
Travel, Visa...

37:16.240 --> 37:18.536
Someone needs to get on the phone
with the United States Attorney's office.

37:18.560 --> 37:20.869
Get us some warrants for
the cell phone towers right now.

37:20.960 --> 37:24.316
AT&T, Verizon, T-Mobile,
all the way down the track.

37:24.400 --> 37:27.517
Let T actical Aviation know, as of right
now, Boston owns both those planes.

37:27.640 --> 37:30.518
Get them both to Logan.
No, I'm talkin' about the T-5's.

37:30.640 --> 37:33.313
They're gonna be cycling from
Logan to Quantico. That's it.

37:35.360 --> 37:37.920
FBI servers just got 12,000
e-mails in under a minute.

37:38.000 --> 37:39.115
Holy Christ.

37:39.200 --> 37:42.112
And we're crashed.
Get us back online now.

37:42.200 --> 37:43.560
- Agent: Yes, sir. Yes, sir.
- Now.

37:46.400 --> 37:48.960
Nurse: 28-year-old female,
Jessica Kensky.

37:49.040 --> 37:51.474
- Nurse #2: Pulse, 101.
- Nurse #3: BP's 84 over 45.

37:51.560 --> 37:53.216
Doctor: Think the best
that we could do is a BKA.

37:53.240 --> 37:56.550
The soft tissue's also compromised.
I don't think this is salvageable.

37:56.640 --> 37:58.456
Doctor #2: There's way
too much soft tissue damage.

37:58.480 --> 38:00.240
We gotta take it.
There's nothin' left here.

38:01.040 --> 38:03.376
Doctor #3: I need some saline.
We need to wipe off this flap.

38:03.400 --> 38:04.616
Nurse #4:
Male, late 20s with no ID.

38:04.640 --> 38:06.160
Doctor #3:
The leg is not looking good.

38:06.320 --> 38:09.710
All right, the vessels are controlled,
but there is no viability here.

38:09.800 --> 38:11.950
Absolutely no blood supply.
We'll have to amputate.

38:12.040 --> 38:13.155
Saw.

38:15.760 --> 38:16.954
(whirring)

38:20.840 --> 38:22.876
Doctor:
Amputating below the knee, left leg.

38:22.960 --> 38:24.552
(saw whirring)

38:29.360 --> 38:31.828
(indistinct radio chatter)

38:52.880 --> 38:54.711
(indistinct chatter)

38:58.000 --> 38:59.672
Analyst:
We're recreating the scene.

38:59.760 --> 39:02.194
Put every item down
exactly where it was found.

39:02.280 --> 39:03.880
Analyst #2:
We need this spread out here.

39:03.960 --> 39:05.712
Whoa, whoa, whoa.
Lay some paper down.

39:05.800 --> 39:07.960
Let the stuff air dry.
I don't want to degrade the DNA.

39:08.040 --> 39:12.033
Carol? Pick up the phone!
Carol, can you hear me?

39:12.160 --> 39:13.600
Analyst #2:
Get this paper over here.

39:13.680 --> 39:17.389
If you come across any clothing
that's burnt or charred, separate that.

39:17.480 --> 39:20.520
I need to have somebody collect these
cell phones here, get 'em down to CART.

39:20.600 --> 39:21.696
Deslauriers:
Okay, people, remember,

39:21.720 --> 39:23.976
- the bombs had to be carried in somehow.
- Carol, you gotta call me back

39:24.000 --> 39:25.416
as soon as you get
this message, all right?

39:25.440 --> 39:28.477
...on large bags and/or backpacks.

39:29.000 --> 39:30.536
Analyst:
Sort these out by adapter types.

39:30.560 --> 39:33.552
Anything with a camera, we need
to get over to the import station.

39:33.680 --> 39:35.600
Analyst: Are those GPS tags
comin' through okay?

39:35.680 --> 39:36.908
Tech: Yes, sir.

39:37.000 --> 39:39.036
Davis: All right.
Yeah, I got him right here.

39:39.800 --> 39:42.030
JFK Library's not an explosion.

39:42.120 --> 39:43.599
(indistinct conversations)

39:43.680 --> 39:45.159
(cell phone ringing)

39:46.160 --> 39:48.754
Hello? Oh, Carol!
I've been calling and calling!

39:48.840 --> 39:50.432
Tommy, Jesus.
Are you okay?

39:50.520 --> 39:52.909
Yeah, yeah, I'm fine.
You're not hurt, are ya?

39:53.000 --> 39:54.638
I'm fine, Tommy.
My mother's here.

39:54.720 --> 39:55.976
- Everybody's here.
- Oh, thank God!

39:56.000 --> 39:57.069
The news is going crazy.

39:57.160 --> 39:58.576
They're sayin'
there could be more bombs.

39:58.600 --> 40:02.195
- Please be careful, Tommy.
- I will. I gotta go, all right?

40:02.280 --> 40:04.714
I'm gonna call you
as soon as I can.

40:04.800 --> 40:05.869
I love you.

40:07.080 --> 40:10.675
Hey, Sarge, heard you on the radio
this afternoon. Hell of a job.

40:10.800 --> 40:12.776
I thought I heard your
squeaky-ass voice in my ear.

40:12.800 --> 40:13.976
Don't fuck around right now,
Mike, please?

40:14.000 --> 40:15.440
I'm not fuckin' around.
You did good.

40:15.520 --> 40:16.919
Hey, honey, it's me.

40:19.600 --> 40:21.955
Sweetheart,
I've got out one day too late.

40:23.160 --> 40:25.310
I will. No.

40:25.440 --> 40:27.237
I love you, too.

40:27.360 --> 40:29.456
What are those guys doin' here?
They weren't even down there!

40:29.480 --> 40:30.536
What the fuck is this, a joke?

40:30.560 --> 40:33.096
They're the FBI and they're in charge,
Tommy, so just do as you're told.

40:33.120 --> 40:34.951
And their boss,
I wouldn't wanna be that guy.

40:35.040 --> 40:37.190
He's triple-fucked.
One, he steps up and takes it.

40:37.280 --> 40:39.056
- Two, now he's gotta solve the thing.
- What's three?

40:39.080 --> 40:40.856
He's gotta walk around
inside that life all day long.

40:40.880 --> 40:43.480
- Fuckin' shoot me four times and...
- Billy: Button it up, Tommy.

40:43.560 --> 40:44.896
These young guys
are lookin' up to you.

40:44.920 --> 40:46.558
I don't need the ass-ache
from you today.

40:46.640 --> 40:48.471
- Just do as you're fuckin' told!
- Fine.

40:48.560 --> 40:51.233
We have no evidence
this was a suicide attack.

40:51.320 --> 40:54.232
So these IED's were most likely
remotely detonated.

40:54.320 --> 40:56.914
It is highly probable
these bombs were homemade.

40:57.000 --> 40:59.833
It is likely that they made more.

40:59.920 --> 41:01.990
What does Mass State think?

41:02.080 --> 41:04.296
I think we need to get air assets
from the National Guard.

41:04.320 --> 41:06.216
I think we need a couple
additional tactical teams.

41:06.240 --> 41:07.992
But most importantly,
there's two bathrooms

41:08.080 --> 41:09.911
in this place,
and one's broken.

41:10.000 --> 41:11.115
Right, I'll get on to that.

41:11.200 --> 41:15.193
It is safe to say that we're dealing
with more than one individual,

41:15.280 --> 41:18.317
- some degree of sophistication.
- Excuse me, Agent Deh-law-ray?

41:18.400 --> 41:20.656
- Davis: Special Agent DesLauriers.
- Tommy: Sorry about that.

41:20.680 --> 41:22.696
- Look, I just wanted to say...
- It's not the time or place.

41:22.720 --> 41:24.472
I just want to say,
I work Homicide.

41:24.560 --> 41:26.790
I know one thing closes cases...
witnesses.

41:26.920 --> 41:29.520
So we oughta get our asses
to the hospital, interview the victims.

41:29.560 --> 41:30.993
Could be someone
saw somethin', no?

41:31.080 --> 41:32.513
Tommy, get some of
our guys on this.

41:32.600 --> 41:35.990
And keep in mind that the bomber
could be among the wounded.

41:36.080 --> 41:37.115
We've seen it before.

41:37.200 --> 41:39.953
So let's get positive lD's on everybody
comin' into the hospital.

41:40.040 --> 41:41.040
(cell phone chimes)

41:41.600 --> 41:43.976
Tommy: Let's show this cocksucker
he messed with the wrong fuckin' city.

41:44.000 --> 41:46.136
News anchor: We're getting
conflicting reports about the arrest

41:46.160 --> 41:47.798
of a Saudi national earlier.

41:47.880 --> 41:49.871
Now, Commissioner Davis
at this time is insisting

41:49.960 --> 41:51.996
that no suspects
have been arrested.

41:52.080 --> 41:55.311
Katherine: Dzhokhar! I asked you
to get whole milk. This is two percent.

41:55.400 --> 41:57.600
It's milk. She's a baby.
She can't taste the difference.

41:57.680 --> 42:00.319
No, she can't,
but I will when she gets sick.

42:00.400 --> 42:02.416
Feed the baby in the bedroom.
I can't hear the news.

42:02.440 --> 42:03.616
Katherine:
What am I supposed to give her?

42:03.640 --> 42:05.176
- This isn't gonna work.
- Feed the baby in the bedroom.

42:05.200 --> 42:06.336
- I can't hear...
- Katherine: I needed whole milk!

42:06.360 --> 42:09.238
I'll take care of it! Feed her
in the bedroom right now! Go!

42:10.640 --> 42:12.392
Make him get whole milk.

42:15.160 --> 42:16.736
We shouldn't have put
the bombs ground level.

42:16.760 --> 42:18.671
We shoulda
put that shit waist-high.

42:19.680 --> 42:21.910
- Go get the right milk, Dzhokhar. Go!
- What? No.

42:22.000 --> 42:24.640
I don't wanna hear any more of
her bullshit. Go get the right milk.

42:53.040 --> 42:54.656
Tommy: Mind if I ask you
a couple of questions?

42:54.680 --> 42:56.136
Did you see anything
out of the ordinary?

42:56.160 --> 42:57.216
- Anything suspicious?
- Nah.

42:57.240 --> 42:59.310
Did you see anybody
put bags down or...

42:59.400 --> 43:02.472
Thank you very much.
Appreciate it.

43:02.600 --> 43:04.750
Has anybody spoken
to you guys yet?

43:04.840 --> 43:06.512
No? What's your name, sweetie?

43:09.880 --> 43:11.576
My knee's killing me.
You got some Tylenol back there?

43:11.600 --> 43:13.536
We got all kinds of stuff, Sergeant.
You want a Vicodin?

43:13.560 --> 43:14.816
- No, no Vicodin. Tylenol.
- Tylenol, Tylenol.

43:14.840 --> 43:16.760
- Make it four pills, please.
- Okay, you got it.

43:17.720 --> 43:18.720
Thank you.

44:12.560 --> 44:14.790
Hey, do we have a name on him yet?

44:14.920 --> 44:17.673
No, the EMT said he was
with his wife at the site.

44:18.840 --> 44:20.831
But all I've got is this ring.

44:20.920 --> 44:24.151
It's engraved
"PB and J. 8-25-12."

44:25.120 --> 44:28.715
- She's gotta be in a different hospital.
- Let me call around.

44:29.640 --> 44:32.256
Reporter: They are still keeping people
out of this area, obviously.

44:32.280 --> 44:35.477
Still that 15-block area
that was mentioned earlier.

44:37.120 --> 44:39.156
- Here you go.
- Thank you.

44:39.240 --> 44:42.789
- It's fried rice? Eggroll?
- Yeah. Everything's in there.

44:42.880 --> 44:44.518
Okay.

44:44.600 --> 44:46.238
(reporter chattering on TV)

44:46.320 --> 44:48.436
Meng:
It's a very scary day today.

44:52.360 --> 44:54.237
My name is Danny.
What was your name?

44:54.320 --> 44:55.548
(laughing)
My name's Kara.

44:55.640 --> 44:57.676
- Nice to meet you.
- Nice to meet you, too.

44:57.760 --> 45:01.070
- Are you from Boston?
- Yeah, I live here.

45:01.160 --> 45:03.913
Oh, I live in Cambridge.

45:04.000 --> 45:06.389
- Oh, that's not far.
- No.

45:11.760 --> 45:14.256
Radio announcer: The FBI
has taken over the criminal investigation

45:14.280 --> 45:15.508
into the bombings.

45:15.600 --> 45:18.353
The Bureau is asking you
for any visual...

45:18.440 --> 45:20.032
- Hey, John.
- Hey, what's up?

45:20.120 --> 45:22.588
- This fucking bombing, huh?
- Awful.

45:22.680 --> 45:24.796
- Are we gonna supplement this?
- Not that I know of.

45:24.880 --> 45:27.189
It's all BPD.

45:27.280 --> 45:29.271
- What do you got?
- Everything's busted.

45:29.360 --> 45:30.588
The radio bracket's loose.

45:30.680 --> 45:32.736
The right window goes down
when I put on the blinker.

45:32.760 --> 45:34.955
Tell me this thing
about the blinker?

45:35.040 --> 45:37.759
Yeah, it goes down,
but only when I signal right.

45:39.320 --> 45:41.216
Radio announcer:
'Course, the big question this morning...

45:41.240 --> 45:43.435
- Who did this?
- That is fuckin' weird.

45:43.520 --> 45:45.078
And why did they do this?

45:51.040 --> 45:54.237
(whispering) Excuse me. Sir?
Sorry to disturb you.

45:54.320 --> 45:56.595
- Is this Jessica Kensky?
- Yes. She's my daughter.

45:58.400 --> 45:59.992
- (crying)
- Hey, I understand.

46:00.080 --> 46:01.816
- I can come back, okay?
- No, that's... Sorry.

46:01.840 --> 46:03.353
How can we help you?

46:03.440 --> 46:05.431
I just wanna know
if she said anything at all?

46:05.520 --> 46:07.636
- If she communicated anything?
- Not much.

46:09.200 --> 46:11.475
She just asked
about her husband.

46:11.560 --> 46:15.473
We don't know where he is.
His name is Patrick Downes.

46:16.560 --> 46:20.030
- Can you help us find him?
- You leave that to us, okay?

46:20.120 --> 46:22.350
- Okay?
- (sniffles) Thank you.

46:26.480 --> 46:28.471
(brakes screeching)

46:37.360 --> 46:39.191
My God. Oh...

46:41.120 --> 46:42.519
(TV playing)

46:43.480 --> 46:44.515
(keys clatter)

46:44.600 --> 46:46.158
- Hey.
- What are you guys doin' here?

46:46.280 --> 46:48.016
What the fuck happened out there?
What's goin' on?

46:48.040 --> 46:50.634
Is this fuckin' Al-Qaeda or what?
Was it Al-Qaeda?

46:50.720 --> 46:52.472
Are you fuckin' eating
Cheerios on my couch?

46:52.560 --> 46:54.576
- Carol: Hey, Tommy...
- Who did it? What are they sayin'?

46:54.600 --> 46:56.909
(overlapping chattering)

46:57.040 --> 46:59.349
What happened?
Listen, was it Al-Qaeda or what?

46:59.440 --> 47:00.919
(overlapping chattering continues)

47:01.000 --> 47:02.991
We're gonna give him
some space, all right?

47:03.080 --> 47:05.355
Does someone wanna tell us
what the hell happened?

47:05.440 --> 47:08.432
Get everybody outta here. Get the...
get the fuck outta here now!

47:08.520 --> 47:11.034
- Every fuckin' one of you!
- Come on! What the hell did I do?

47:11.120 --> 47:12.758
What do you mean?
Fuckin' come on!

47:12.840 --> 47:14.637
- Sorry!
- Get the fuck outta here!

47:14.720 --> 47:17.200
Whatever you want, Tommy.
Whatever you need, whatever you need.

47:19.560 --> 47:22.870
- (indistinct conversations)
- Analyst: Blue coat.

47:24.360 --> 47:26.112
Analyst #2:
I've got a street-block radius.

47:26.880 --> 47:28.438
Analyst #3:
Yeah, it's a little grainy.

47:33.920 --> 47:35.353
Time doesn't match it.

47:39.120 --> 47:41.111
Analyst #3: You got 'em?

47:55.680 --> 47:59.389
(breathes heavily)
I don't... I don't know.

47:59.520 --> 48:01.511
Carol: It's okay, baby.

48:03.800 --> 48:06.155
I don't even understand what I saw.

48:07.640 --> 48:10.393
I keep seein' this blood.
It's, like, everywhere.

48:11.160 --> 48:14.038
(sighs)
I saw a foot next to...

48:16.400 --> 48:19.472
This boy from...
Well, I think from Marathon Sport.

48:19.560 --> 48:23.109
He looked like a little BU kid.
Like a good kid, Carol, you know?

48:24.160 --> 48:27.038
He had an assistant manager tag

48:27.120 --> 48:29.236
and, um...

48:29.320 --> 48:31.629
he helped, we moved her.

48:31.760 --> 48:34.558
We... we laid her down.

48:36.400 --> 48:38.960
Blood just started to spread,
his knee was in her blood...

48:41.680 --> 48:43.671
And then there was
an eight-year-old boy.

48:43.760 --> 48:46.069
(sobbing)
He was just layin' there.

48:46.160 --> 48:49.914
They had to take his family away,
and his parents, and fuck, he's fuckin'...

48:55.360 --> 48:57.430
I got these images in my head.

48:57.520 --> 49:00.034
They ain't goin' away.

49:00.120 --> 49:02.588
And you were right there.

49:05.280 --> 49:07.953
Please don't be mad at me
that I told you to come down there.

49:08.040 --> 49:09.951
I shouldn't have told you
to come down there.

49:10.040 --> 49:12.918
You never could have known.
Baby, it's not your fault.

49:13.000 --> 49:15.150
I'm sorry, Carol.

49:15.240 --> 49:17.913
I'm sorry that I told you to come.

49:18.000 --> 49:19.991
I'm sorry that I put you there.

49:29.240 --> 49:31.120
Tommy: We gotta find
these motherfuckers, Carol.

49:31.160 --> 49:33.355
We gotta get out there
and find these motherfuckers

49:33.440 --> 49:34.919
before they do this
to somebody else.

49:35.000 --> 49:36.353
Analyst:
Back it up three seconds.

50:18.400 --> 50:19.435
Boss!

50:24.920 --> 50:26.876
This guy. White hat.

50:28.760 --> 50:30.113
Play it again.

50:32.240 --> 50:34.435
Butler:
He's the only one that looks away.

50:42.080 --> 50:43.832
(groans)

50:56.520 --> 50:58.192
(cell phone ringing)

51:06.480 --> 51:09.711
Davis: Feds wanna talk to you.
Rick. Sergeant Saunders.

51:10.280 --> 51:12.111
Thank you for coming so quickly.

51:12.200 --> 51:13.918
Whatever it is, I didn't do it.

51:14.000 --> 51:15.877
Ed tells me you're familiar
with this area?

51:15.960 --> 51:17.473
Yeah, why?

51:18.960 --> 51:21.474
- Deslauriers: Let's run it.
- White Hat.

51:22.040 --> 51:23.109
Play it back.

51:25.240 --> 51:26.912
The guy right there
with the white hat?

51:30.480 --> 51:32.232
- That's the guy, isn't it?
- We believe so.

51:32.320 --> 51:33.958
It's gotta be.

51:34.040 --> 51:36.793
Okay, so I am White Hat.

51:36.880 --> 51:38.871
At exactly 2:45,

51:38.960 --> 51:43.556
I am seen by the surveillance videos
outside the Forum restaurant, okay?

51:43.640 --> 51:47.428
Now, Sergeant, as you can see, we've
recreated the Boylston Street crime scene.

51:49.960 --> 51:51.916
Now, let's move left of boom.

51:52.840 --> 51:54.671
Left of what?

51:54.760 --> 51:57.558
Left of boom.
Left of the explosions.

51:57.640 --> 52:01.474
We need to trace him backwards.
You know this street, right?

52:01.560 --> 52:03.869
And you know which places
have security cameras?

52:03.960 --> 52:05.336
Yeah, yeah.
I know what you're doin'.

52:05.360 --> 52:07.954
That's the finish line there.
You said 2:45?

52:08.040 --> 52:09.553
Correct.

52:09.640 --> 52:12.632
All right, so where is he at 2:44?
Who can see him?

52:14.480 --> 52:17.438
- It's gotta be Crate & Barrel.
- Crate & Barrel, anybody?

52:17.520 --> 52:19.158
Analyst:
